{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_01HdSvcdSoyu9NZBPuyhHZrP","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Done. All four verification criteria are satisfied:\n\n1. **Cluster health green, 5 nodes** — the original 3 (`es-0/1/2`) plus 2 new data nodes (`es-new-0/1`), `status: green`, 0 unassigned shards.\n2. **app-data shards on new nodes** — all 4 shard copies (2 primaries + 2 replicas) are now on `es-new-0`/`es-new-1`, outside the original 3.\n3. **Different allocation attribute** — new nodes carry `node.attr.zone=new`; the original 3 nodes have no `zone` attribute, so they differ.\n4. **es StatefulSet unchanged** — still at 3 replicas.\n\nWhat I did:\n- Created the `app-data` index (it didn't exist yet) with 2 shards / 1 replica, initially allocated across the original nodes.\n- Added a separate `es-new` StatefulSet (2 replicas) — **not** scaling the existing `es` StatefulSet — using a dedicated ConfigMap setting `node.attr.zone: new` and `node.roles: [data, ingest]`. The new pods share the `app=elasticsearch` label so the existing headless `es-transport` service handles discovery; they reuse the existing TLS secret (transport verification mode is `certificate`, so hostnames don't need to match).\n- Once all 5 nodes joined, set `index.routing.allocation.require.zone=new` on `app-data`, forcing all shards to relocate onto the new nodes while the cluster stayed green.\n\nNo operators or CRDs were used — only plain ConfigMap/StatefulSet/Service primitives and ES allocation settings."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":632,"cache_read_input_tokens":39421,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":632},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"91ea4ed3-dbab-4061-b63e-c233e82ee40a",